    "ts": "2026-06-04T00:49:04+00:00",
    "headline": "Meta accuses Australia of breaching FTA, invokes US 'trade action'",
    "summary": "Meta accused Australia of violating a free trade agreement with the U.S. by proposing a new tax on certain tech giants which do not ‌strike licensing deals with local media, escalating a dispute which has simmered for half a decade.  The $1.6 ‌trillion Facebook and Instagram owner said a proposal to tax platforms 2.25% of all Australian revenue - including revenue unrelated to social media - ​was \"indefensible\" and went further than actions which had prompted a response by the U.S. government.  Meta has previously said it opposed the so-called news bargaining incentive, for which Australia's centre-left government is considering industry submissions.",
